error.signature: Error response from daemon: manifest for image:tag not found: manifest unknown

verdict.summary: The specified image tag does not exist in the registry.

dead_ends.action: Pulling without specifying a tag (defaults to :latest)
dead_ends.why_fails: latest tag may not exist; many repos don't publish it
The image might exist in the specified registry but with a different tag

workarounds.action: Check available tags: docker manifest inspect <image> or visit the registry's web UI
workarounds.how: Verify the exact tag name â€” tags are case-sensitive

workarounds.action: For multi-arch images, specify the platform: docker pull --platform linux/amd64 <image:tag>
workarounds.how: Some tags only exist for specific architectures

frequently_confused_with.distinction: 'response from daemon' indicates a missing Docker image tag or manifest, while 'WARNING' indicates a pip root user warning in Docker.
